===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|はぎ}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|はぎ|tr=pagi₁|sort=はぎ}}. Attested in {{w|Shōsōin documents}} from 740 with the spelling {{lang|ja|波岐}} (''pagi₁'').<ref name="JDBhagi">{{R:JDB|page=573}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2Ohagi"/> Also attested in the ''{{w|Fudoki|Hitachi no kuni Fudoki}}'' in the form {{m|ja|やつかはぎ|夜都賀波岐|tr=ya-tuka-pagi₁|t=indigenous people < a person with a long shin}}.<ref name="JDBhagi"/> In turn, reconstructed as deriving from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*panki|sort=はぎ}}.

As seen below, the pitch accent of this word in the Heian period contains a rising pitch in the first syllable, and Ryukyuan cognates show reflexes of proto-Ryukyuan class C, which is rare for class 3 accent words, hinting at some kind of contraction.

